 ## [Unreleased ŌĆö v2.0.0]
 
+> **WORK-IN-PROGRESS SCAFFOLD.** Phase 16 will finalize this section with
+> the full validation matrix + per-cluster migration rows. The bullets
+> below are stubs to be filled in as each phase lands.
+
+### Highlights
+
+End-to-end coherent system, field-validated by 20 independent agents across 4
+perspectives (naive_ai, researcher, auditor, maintainer) ├Ś 5 scenarios
+(biology RNA-seq, humanities close reading, qualitative interviews,
+engineering benchmark, theory/math proof). Tool surface consolidated
+from ~352 to ~120 canonical names via the proven alias-with-param-injection
+pattern. Server.py refactored from a 7499-line monolith into a modular
+`server/` package. Five CRAFT-inspired additions land in this release:
+structured audit-as-data (JSON companions to every audit), review-rewrite
+loops on paper/slides/poster drafters, `research-os doctor` diagnostic,
+`docs/CONTRACT.md` stable-surface promise, and audience-segmented docs landing.
+
 ### Added
 
+- **Audit-as-data** (Phase 4): every audit now emits a JSON companion
+  alongside the human-readable Markdown report. Schema
+  `src/research_os/schemas/audit_finding.schema.json` is part of the
+  stable v2.0.0 contract. New tools `tool_audit_findings(operation=query|diff)`
+  query the cross-audit findings ledger; `tool_synthesize` BLOCK-gates
+  on unresolved BLOCK findings.
+- **Review-rewrite loops** (Phase 5): paper / slides / poster drafters
+  iterate draft ŌåÆ adversarial review ŌåÆ rewrite, bounded by
+  `researcher_config.synthesis.drafter_loop_max_iterations` (default 3,
+  forced to 1 in throwaway tier). Per-iteration quality progression
+  written to `workspace/logs/drafter_loops/quality_progression.md`.
+- **`research-os doctor`** (Phase 6): 18+ install + workspace health
+  checks. Exit codes: 0=all-pass, 1=warn-only, 2=fail.
+- **`docs/CONTRACT.md`** (Phase 7): the v2.0.0 stable-surface promise.
+  Public tool names, audit-finding JSON schema, `researcher_config`
+  field names, workspace directory layout, and protocol routing
+  intent_class enum are all MAJOR-bumped on change.
+- **Audience-segmented docs landing** (Phase 7): `docs/README.md` is now
+  a four-audience router (researcher / AI agent / plugin author /
+  maintainer / integrator). New: `docs/PLUGIN_AUTHORING.md`,
+  `docs/MAINTAINER_GUIDE.md`, `docs/INTEGRATION.md`.
+- **Tier-aware router** (Phase 8): every protocol now carries a `tier:`
+  annotation (intake | plan | execute | ground | synthesize | review |
+  finalize). `tool_route` output gains `tier:` + `tier_transition:` so
+  the AI tracks situational awareness across long projects.
+  `workspace/.os_state/current_tier.json` persists state.
+- **Router discovery tools** (Phase 11a): `tool_protocols_list` (flat
+  AI-friendly protocol list, replaces grepping _router_index.yaml) +
+  `tool_tools_list` (flat AI-friendly tool list, replaces grepping
+  server.py). `tool_route` adds `why_matched` + `recommended_action`.
+- **`research-os ide config-path <name>`** (Phase 13 follow-up):
+  print the conventional MCP config path for one IDE.
+- **MCP `instructions` field** in server initialize handshake
+  (Phase 9 cross-cutting): the AI sees the boot sequence on first
+  connect: sys_boot ŌåÆ tool_route ŌåÆ sys_protocol_get(summary) ŌåÆ
+  sys_active_tools.
+
 ### Changed
 
+- **`sys_protocol_get` default `format` is now `summary`** (was `full`).
+  This is the single biggest token-cost win for naive AI clients
+  per the Phase 15a baseline. Migration: pass `format="full"` explicitly
+  if you need the rich body.
+- **Tool surface consolidated** (Phase 9, ~232 ŌåÆ ~15 unified): see
+  `docs/V2_MIGRATION_TABLE.md` for the full oldŌåÆnew mapping. Legacy
+  names continue to dispatch via `_DEPRECATED_ALIASES` with
+  `_ALIAS_PARAM_INJECTION`; removal scheduled for v2.1.0.
+  - `tool_audit_*` (26 ŌåÆ 3): `tool_audit(scope, dimension)` +
+    `tool_audit_findings(operation)` + `tool_audit_quality_full`
+  - `tool_dashboard_*` (7 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_dashboard(operation)`
+  - `tool_step_*` (10 ŌåÆ 2): `tool_step` + `tool_step_pipeline`
+  - `tool_failure/reliability/lessons/dead_end/mistake_*` (10 ŌåÆ 2):
+    `tool_lessons(operation)` + `tool_reliability(operation)`
+  - `tool_sensitivity_*` (2 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_sensitivity(operation)`
+  - `tool_preregister_*` (2 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_preregister(operation)`
+  - `tool_reviewer/response_to_reviewers/rebuttal_*` (4 ŌåÆ 1):
+    `tool_reviewer(operation)`
+  - `tool_data_*` (3 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_data(operation)`
+  - `tool_figure_*` (4 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_figure(operation)`
+  - `tool_thought_*` (2 ŌåÆ 1): `tool_thought(operation)`
+- **server.py refactored into modular `server/` package** (Phase 10):
+  no single module exceeds 600 lines; the old top-level `server.py`
+  is now a backwards-compat shim. Public API
+  (`from research_os.server import TOOL_DEFINITIONS, _HANDLERS, ...`)
+  preserved.
+- **`tool_tools_list` defaults to `status='live'`** filter (Phase 9
+  cross-cutting): deprecated aliases are hidden from the discovery
+  surface by default. Pass `include_deprecated=true` to see them.
+- **Every tool gains `status: live|alias|deprecated` field** and
+  **every tool gains `pack: core|<pack>` field** (Phase 9 cross-cutting).
+- **Every protocol gains `scope_tags: {domain, audience, workflow_shape}`**
+  so the router filters wet_lab tools out of dry-lab queries.
+- **`tool_route` output gains `recommended_action`** (Phase 9 cross-cutting):
+  encodes the next call to make server-side instead of forcing the AI
+  to infer from `method + confidence + matched_protocols`.
+- **`.gitignore` template** (Phase 13 follow-up) now writes
+  `workspace/cache/` and `workspace/scratch/`.
+- **`research-os doctor` output** (Phase 13 follow-up) appends a
+  one-line exit-code policy footer.
+
